# WorkOrderBlender - Core Development Rules

## Essential Project Constraints
- **Project Name**: WorkOrderBlender - Work Order SDF Consolidator
- **Framework**: .NET Framework 4.8 Windows Forms application (x64 only)
- **Database Rule**: NEVER modify source databases - READ-ONLY access only
- **Schema**: Destination database schema in [resources/wo_schema.xml](mdc:resources/wo_schema.xml)

## Critical Development Standards
- **Use native .NET Framework 4.8 components** whenever possible
- **DEBUG logging is enabled** - use [Program.Log()](mdc:Program.cs) extensively
- **Single-line comments** are required for code understanding
- **Keep code DRY and robust** - eliminate redundant code
- **Reuse existing functionality** over implementing new features
- **Remove unused functions** - clean up dead code

## Code Organization Principles
- Shared functionality goes in utility libraries
- Main application logic in [MainForm.cs](mdc:MainForm.cs)
- Configuration management via [UserConfig.cs](mdc:UserConfig.cs)
- Database utilities in [SqlCeUtils.cs](mdc:SqlCeUtils.cs)
- Edit tracking in [InMemoryEditStore.cs](mdc:InMemoryEditStore.cs)

## Error Handling Mandate
- All operations wrapped in try-catch blocks
- Graceful degradation - never crash the application
- User-friendly error messages via MessageBox
- Comprehensive logging of all errors and debug information
